description.narrative: The Middle East Economic Growth (MEG) Best Practices activity is a new, buy-in field support mechanism to provide ME Bureau field operating units with knowledge, tools, and best practices to promote economic growth, financial management, and business expansion effectively in the MENA region across a variety of operating contexts and in response to a variety of economic growth needs. MEG will support requests from the ME Bureau field operating units for assessments and diagnostics, program designs and model scopes of work, technical briefs and case studies, and pilot and bridge activities. Knowledge-sharing is a central focus of the mechanism; activities will promote economic growth best practices in policy, processes, and capacity building.
